{"word":"H1551 - גָּלִיל - Gâlîyl - gaw-leel' - Galilee","slug":"H1551","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">גָּלִיל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Gâlîyl"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>gaw-leel'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Galilee"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>גּלילה גּליל</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>gâlı̂yl gâlı̂ylâh</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>gaw-leel'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Galilee = \"circuit, district\" <ol><li>a territory in Naphtali largely occupied by heathen; a circuit of towns around Kedesh-Naphtali, in which were situated the 20 towns given by Solomon to Hiram king of Tyre as payment for his work in conveying timber from Lebanon to Jerusalem</li></ol> <p />Origin: the same as <a href=\"#/H1550\">H1550</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Location "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1019\">H1019</a>, <a href=\"#/H1530\">H1530</a>, <a href=\"#/H1531\">H1531</a>, <a href=\"#/H1534\">H1534</a>, <a href=\"#/H1536\">H1536</a>, <a href=\"#/H1537\">H1537</a>, <a href=\"#/H1538\">H1538</a>, <a href=\"#/H1543\">H1543</a>, <a href=\"#/H1544\">H1544</a>, <a href=\"#/H1550\">H1550</a>, <a href=\"#/H1552\">H1552</a>, <a href=\"#/H1553\">H1553</a>, <a href=\"#/H1554\">H1554</a>, <a href=\"#/H1556\">H1556</a>, <a href=\"#/H1557\">H1557</a>, <a href=\"#/H1559\">H1559</a>, <a href=\"#/H1561\">H1561</a>, <a href=\"#/H1562\">H1562</a>, <a href=\"#/H1567\">H1567</a>, <a href=\"#/H4039\">H4039</a>"}]}